order=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105142459127064>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Horses v2.0</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Apr 27th 3:02 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>266 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Ok, I've had a few days to practice with my new steed. Unfortunately, he is about as ignorant as real life horses. Let me explain. <br><br>1. You also cannot duck while on a horse to interrupt spell casting. This is most aggrivating when I go to cast my JBB ( 8.0 sec cast ) and one second into the cast the mob decided to run. I have to chase them and wait for the JBB to cast thru before I can root again.<br>2. The ears arent a big problem, as others said cast invis then reappear or shrink down and the ears disappear. However if remounting the horse you must do this EVERY time. It make targetting and looting corpses unnecessarily difficult IMO.<br>3. My bargain bin horse is slow, something I fully expected, but pulling while on him is alot more difficult than I expected. <br>4. Starting and stopping arent like a ferrari either. This leads to mobs getting in extra hits and stuns on me as I try to lead my horse away from a rooted mob only for him to casually gather his loins to start moving away.<br>5. HP regen should be the same as sitting as mana regen is. I think trolls and iksar would be more pissed about this as at level 60 they have 12/18 hp tick regen standing /sitting. I will say that mana regen is the same as sitting which is nice, and even a cheapo horse is about the same as a FT 8 item.<br><br>59 Ogre Luminary on Luclin server--Chaotic Winds--Venerable Aggrok<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Apr 27 02:32:58 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>3 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105162299143030>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=9&mid=105162299143030>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=105162299143030>RE: Horses v2.0</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=105162299143030#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Apr 29th 10:08 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>214 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is just a bit of an update on my own experience with a mount.&nbsp;&nbsp;Last night was the first time I used my lizard in a group.  Granted, for most of the evening it was low maintenance group, but I did learn a lot about my lizard, Poky.  First of all, Poky really is slow.  I could outrun him without even breathing hard.  Add to this is slow starting and stopping and I really wouldn’t recommend buying a cheap mount for transportation.  If all you want do is move quickly and can’t cast SoW, quest yourself some JBoots.<br><br>Another annoying aspect to being mounted is trying to loot.  A lot of our combat was taking place on hilly terrain. And the majority of the time I couldn’t loot mobs from Poky’s back.  I’m not sure if this is a problem on even ground.  The fact that I had Dead Man Floating on all night could have added to this problem.  But we were fighting vampires that liked to turn invisible and we were also running across mountains, so the spell came in very handy.  <br><br>Other than movement and looting, I didn’t have any other problems with my new pet.  And both these problems can be fairly easily solved.  All I had to do was click off my pet icon and dismount.  When we reached our destination or I finished looting I would open my inventory and click on my drum to remount.  The cast time is only three seconds, so it’s not really a big deal.<br><br>Now to praise Poky.  Sitting on his back made a big difference in my manna regeneration.  I had KEI at the start of the group and for a long time I didn’t even have to cast cannibalization because I was regenerating manna even while all the action was going on.  This in itself was really nice, but I truly came to love my new pet when my KEI ran out and I had to start cannibalizing like crazy.  <br><br>Unless you haven’t received your cannibalization spell yet, I don’t have to tell you guys what a pain it is to constantly keep your eye on your manna bar and jump up and down over and over and over again to get ever drop of manna you can.  Well, with Poky I don’t have to do that any more, at least not when I’m outside.  I just sat there and hit the spell icon again and again as soon as it refreshed.  When my health hit about 25 to 30% I cast my stoicism spell and I was good to go.  This really came into play when we pulled a very nasty winged vampire.  I was the healer of the group and the vampire was tearing up our warrior.  I’d cast stoicism and a superior healing on her, dot the mob and then canni my manna back.  When my health got low I’d cast stoicism on myself as well.  The fight was a long one but I never ran out of manna.  I was amazed at how quickly I could regen my manna when I didn’t have to bounce up and down all the time.  <br><br>After last night I have no regrets about blowing every copper I had on a mount.  It was more than worth it.  I wouldn’t give Poky up for anything.  My only regret is that I won’t be able to use him indoors.  <br></p>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 62nd Season<br><b>Jondor</b><br>Barbarian Beastlord, 54th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></td></tr>
